<BaseLayout title="Homelab / GitOps / Automation | Franco Lopez" description="Franco Lopez's homelab and automation work across Kubernetes, GitOps, Talos, Proxmox, Docker, Raspberry Pi, and repeatable infrastructure patterns.">
  <header class="page-header">
    <span class="eyebrow">hands-on lab · repeatable infrastructure</span>
    <h1>Homelab / GitOps / Automation</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      A practical lab for testing infrastructure ideas before turning them into writing, scripts, or
      production patterns.
    </p>
  </header>

  <article class="content">
    <h2>Focus</h2>
    <p>
      The goal is not to collect tools. The goal is to build repeatable patterns I can explain, break,
      fix, document, and defend in an interview or production discussion.
    </p>

    <h2>Areas I’m working through</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Kubernetes and container operations</li>
      <li>GitOps workflows and deployment automation</li>
      <li>Talos, Proxmox, Docker, and Raspberry Pi infrastructure</li>
      <li>Linux administration and shell automation</li>
      <li>Networking, storage, secrets, and monitoring patterns</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How this should show up on the site</h2>
    <p>
      Homelab work should support the career story without taking over the site. The best version is a
      steady stream of short posts: what I built, what broke, what I changed, and what I learned.
    </p>
  </article>
